{"title_page": "Candice Glover", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name = Candice Glover\n| image = Life Ball 2014 red carpet 092 Candice Glover.jpg\n| caption = Candice Glover in 2014\n| background = solo_singer\n| birth_name = Candice Rickelle Glover\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1989|11|22}}\n| birth_place = [[Beaufort, South Carolina]]\n| origin = [[St. Helena Island, South Carolina]], United States\n| years_active = 2010\u2013present\n| label = [[Interscope Records|Interscope]], [[19 Recordings|19]], [[Independent record label|Independent]]\n| genre = [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]], [[Jazz music|jazz]], [[Pop music|pop]], [[Soul music|soul]]\n| occupation = [[Singing|Singer]], [[songwriter]], [[actress]]\n| instrument = [[Vocals]]\n|website      = {{URL|http://www.candiceglover-official.com }}\n}}\n\n'''Candice Rickelle Glover''' (born November 22, 1989) is an American R&B singer and actress who won the [[American Idol (season 12)|twelfth season]] of ''[[American Idol]]''.<ref name=\"top10\">{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/idol-worship/american-idol-top-10-revealed-426777 |title = 'American Idol': Top 10 Revealed Amid Brutal Eliminations |date=7 March 2013 |accessdate=7 March 2013 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |first=Erin |last=Carlson}}</ref> Glover is the first winner to have auditioned three times before being cast for the live shows. Her debut album ''[[Music Speaks]]'' was released on February 18, 2014.<ref name=\"Hollywood Reporter\">{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/idol-worship/american-idol-candice-glovers-album-639324 |title='American Idol': Candice Glover's Album Delayed |publisher=Hollywood Reporter |date=2013-09-30 |accessdate=2014-08-10}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nCandice Rickelle Glover was born on November 22, 1989 in [[Beaufort, South Carolina]], to John and Carole Glover. She is the oldest of seven children.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.islandpacket.com/2013/02/26/2395399/lowcountry-native-aims-for-top.html |title=Lowcountry native Candice Glover in Top 20 on American Idol |date=26 February 2013 |accessdate=15 March 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130302020117/http://www.islandpacket.com/2013/02/26/2395399/lowcountry-native-aims-for-top.html |archive-date=2 March 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.islandpacket.com/2013/03/03/2400313/candice-glover-goes-back-to-american.html |title = Candice Glover goes back to 'American Idol' for third time with win in mind |date=3 March 2013 |accessdate=15 March 2013}}</ref> She graduated from [[Beaufort High School]] in 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.islandpacket.com/2013/03/15/2421553/hundreds-turn-out-to-beaufort.html |title = VIDEO: Hundreds turn out to Beaufort rally for 'American Idol' contestant Candice Glover |date=15 March 2013}}</ref> Before Idol, Candice was insecure and struggled with her weight. In an interview, she said she had to have counseling at school because of her insecurity issues.\n\n== ''American Idol'' ==\n{{Main|American Idol (season 9)|l1=American Idol seasons 9|American Idol (season 11)|l2=11|American Idol (season 12)|l3=12}}\n\n=== Overview ===\nGlover auditioned in [[Charlotte, North Carolina]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hollywoodlife.com/2013/01/24/american-idol-candice-glover-audition-video-best-this-season/  |title='American Idol': Candice Glover Returns \u2014 'Best Audition This Season' |date= January 23, 2013 |accessdate=March 18, 2013}}</ref> She previously auditioned in the [[American Idol (season 9)|ninth]] and [[American Idol (season 11)|eleventh]] seasons. In the ninth season [[Simon Cowell]] said that he could not see Glover being anything more than a lounge singer and she was cut during the final 70 round. She was eliminated by producers during the ninth season when she forgot the lyrics to her song \"[[Chasing Pavements]]\" by [[Adele]].\n\n=== Season 11 ===\nGlover auditioned in [[Savannah, Georgia]]. She sang \"Blame It on Me\" by [[Chrisette Michele]]. She advanced, but her audition was not aired. In round one, she performed Karina's \"Slow Motion\". In round three, she sang \"[[Someone like You (Adele song)|Someone like You]]\" by [[Adele]], where she received a standing ovation from the judges. She performed \"[[It Doesn't Matter Anymore]]\" by [[Buddy Holly]] with eleventh season finalists [[DeAndre Brackensick]] and [[Jessica Sanchez]] in the group round and was eliminated.\n\n=== Season 12 ===\nDuring her audition for the twelfth season, Glover sang \"[[Syrup & Honey]]\" by [[Duffy (singer)|Duffy]], where she received a standing ovation. Judge [[Randy Jackson]] said that she was the best performer by far in the competition. [[Mariah Carey]] called her singing \"The best singing we have heard thus far.\" Glover advanced to Hollywood. In an interview, she said, \"I thought they were going to get sick of seeing my face.\" For the first round in Hollywood, she sang \"Impossible\" by [[Christina Aguilera]]. For the second round, she performed \"[[Hit Em Up Style]]\" with Kamaria Ousley, Denise Jackson, and Melinda Ademi. This was named the best group the judges had seen all day. In round three, she put a jazzy twist on [[Alicia Keys]]'s \"[[Girl on Fire (song)|Girl on Fire]]\". It was later announced that Glover was one of the top 20 girls of the season and she advanced to Las Vegas. In Vegas, she performed \"[[Natural Woman]]\" by [[Aretha Franklin]]. In the semi-finals of the competition, Glover performed \"[[Ordinary People (John Legend song)|Ordinary People]]\" by [[John Legend]]. On March 7, 2013, she was voted into the Top 10.<ref name=\"top10\"/> Her Top 10 performance of \"[[I (Who Have Nothing)]]\" by [[Ben E. King]] earned her enough votes to land among the night\u2019s top three contestants, along with [[Kree Harrison]] and [[Angie Miller (American singer)|Angie Miller]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://popwatch.ew.com/2013/03/14/american-idol-2013-results-top-10/ |title='American Idol' results: First of Top 10 to go is.... |date=March 14, 2013 |accessdate=March 18, 2013}}</ref> After her Top 6 performances, Glover earned enough votes to land in the night's top two contestants, along with Kree Harrison. She covered \"Lovesong\" by The Cure and broke down in tears after receiving a standing ovation. For the first time, after her Top 4 performance, she landed in the bottom two. On May 16, Glover won the contest and her debut single '[[I Am Beautiful]]' was released to music store outlets.\n\n=== Performances and results ===\n\n==== Season 9 ====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!Episode\n!Theme\n!Song choice\n!Original artist\n!Order #\n!Result\n|-\t\n|Audition\n|Auditioner's Choice\n|colspan=2|Not aired\n|N/A\n|Advanced\n|-\n|Hollywood Round, Part 1\n|A capella\n|colspan=2|Not aired\n|N/A\n|Advanced\n|-\n|Hollywood Round, Part 2\n|Group Performance\n|\"[[Superwoman (Alicia Keys song)|Superwoman]]\"<br /> <small>with Shelby Dressel, Kelsey Laverack Rey, and Audri Vargas</small>\n|[[Alicia Keys]]\n|N/A\n|Advanced\n|-\n|Hollywood Round, Part 3\n|Solo\n|colspan=2|Not aired\n|N/A\n|Eliminated\n|}\n\n==== Season 11 ====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!Episode\n!Theme\n!Song choice\n!Original artist\n!Order #\n!Result\n|-\t\n|Audition\n|Auditioner's Choice\n|\"[[Blame It on Me (Chrisette Michele song)|Blame It on Me]]\"\n|[[Chrisette Michele]]\n|N/A\n|Advanced\n|-\n|Hollywood Round, Part 1\n|A Capella\n|\"[[Slow Motion (Lee.M and J. Pearl song)|Slow Motion]]\"\n|[[Lee Mulhern|Lee.M]] & [[J. Pearl]]\n|N/A\n|Advanced\n|-\n|Hollywood Round, Part 2\n|Group Performance\n|colspan=2|Not aired<br /> <small>with [[Lauren Daigle]], Amber Caparas, Brittany Hammond, and Kalyn McNeil</small>\n|N/A\n|Advanced\n|-\n|Hollywood Round, Part 3\n|Solo\n|\"[[Someone like You (Adele song)|Someone like You]]\"\n|[[Adele]]\n|N/A\n|Advanced\n|-\n|Las Vegas Round\n|Group Performance\n|\"[[It Doesn't Matter Anymore]]\"<br/>with 