declared safe as no one was eliminated.</small>\n*<small>{{note|2|Note 2}} Due to the surprise non-elimination at the top 4, the top 4 remained intact for another week.</small>\n\n== ''Music Speaks'' and upcoming second studio album ==\n[[File:Candice Glover 2013.jpg|Glover singing The Star-Spangled Banner at [[Citi Field]] in 2013|thumb|left]]\nImmediately following the finale broadcast on May 16, 2013, Glover's debut album, ''[[Music Speaks]]'', along with her debut single \"[[I Am Beautiful]]\" was available for pre-order; this was a first for the ''Idol'' series.<ref name=\"Debut\">{{cite news|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/music/posts/la-et-ms-american-idol-winner-candice-glover-to-issue-debut-music-speaks-july-16-20130517,0,2914308.story |title = 'American Idol' winner Candice Glover to issue debut 'Music Speaks' July 16 |date=17 May 2013 |accessdate=17 May 2013 |work=Los Angeles Times |first=Gerrick D. |last=Kennedy}}</ref> On May 17, 2013, Glover performed the single on ''[[The Tonight Show|The Tonight Show with Jay Leno]]''.<ref name=\"Leno\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thestate.com/2013/05/17/2776293/candice-glovers-american-idol.html |title = Candice Glover's American Idol win still sinking in |date=17 May 2013 |accessdate=17 May 2013}}</ref> On May 20, 2013, Glover performed on ''[[Live! with Kelly and Michael]]''.<ref name=\"Live!\">{{cite web |url=http://thehonestyhour.com/2013/05/candice-glover-performs-i-am-beautiful-on-kelly-michael/ |title=Candice Glover Performs 'I Am Beautiful' on 'Kelly & Michael' |date=20 May 2013 |accessdate=20 May 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130608200039/http://thehonestyhour.com/2013/05/candice-glover-performs-i-am-beautiful-on-kelly-michael/ |archivedate=8 June 2013 }}</ref>\nGlover confirmed on May 21, to be working on a more R&B influenced second single to be released.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/CandiceGlover/status/336863574427312128 |title=Twitter / CandiceGlover: Yes :) RT @fernaaaaando95 |publisher=Twitter.com |date= |accessdate=2014-08-10}}</ref>\nIn its first week \"I Am Beautiful\" reached number 33 on [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs]] and number 93 on the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Billboard Hot 100|Hot 100]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/idol-worship/american-idol-charts-candice-glover-555317 | work=The Hollywood Reporter | first=Fred | last=Bronson | title='American Idol' on the Charts: Candice Glover, Kree Harrison Make Their Billboard Debuts | date=23 May 2013}}</ref>\n\nGlover took part in the [[American Idols LIVE! Tour 2013]], beginning on July 19 and ending on August 31, 2013. Her debut album ''[[Music Speaks]]'' was released on February 18, 2014, after being pushed back from the original July 16 and October 8, 2013 dates.<ref>{{cite web |last=Oberle |first=Laura |url=http://www.islandpacket.com/2013/10/08/2727386/candice-glover-album-music-speaks.html |title=Candice Glover album 'Music Speaks' accidentally released Oct. 8 &#124; Candice Glover |publisher=The Island Packet |date=2014-02-26 |accessdate=2014-08-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140807190900/http://www.islandpacket.com/2013/10/08/2727386/candice-glover-album-music-speaks.html |archive-date=2014-08-07 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nGlover's second single from her debut album is called \"Cried,\" and was released on November 25, 2013. \"Cried\" debuted at number 28 on the Billboard Adult R&B chart in January 2014,<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/idol-worship/american-idol-charts-candice-glover-670037 |title='American Idol' on the Charts: Candice Glover Debuts With First Post-Win Single |publisher=Hollywood Reporter |date=2014-01-11 |accessdate=2014-08-10}}</ref> and has peaked at number 18.\n\nGlover has begun work on her second studio album, due out in 2016.<ref name=\"facebook.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/CandiceGloverMusic |title=Candice Glover - Home |website=Facebook.com |date= |accessdate=2020-04-08}}</ref> She is writing all of the material on the album herself. She announced on her Facebook page that the album will be more \"her\" and that there will be a duet with fellow ''Idol'' contestant [[Amber Holcomb]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/CandiceGloverMusic|title=Candice Glover|website=Facebook.com}}</ref>\n\nGlover was also featured on Chadd Black's  single, \"Love No Fear\", which was released on February 14, 2015.<ref name=\"facebook.com\"/> She will be releasing a mixtape with Black sometime in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/CandiceGlover?ref_src=twsrc%5Egoogle%7Ctwcamp%5Eserp%7Ctwgr%5Eauthor|title=Tweets with replies by Candice Glover (@CandiceGlover) - Twitter|website=twitter.com}}</ref> In January 2016, she announced that she had parted ways with 19 Recordings/Interscope. Her new album will be released independently, and she hopes to work with [[Jazmine Sullivan]], [[Chris Brown]], and/or [[Drake (rapper)|Drake]] on it.<ref>{{cite web|title = INTERVIEW: Candice Glover Talks Life After Winning 'American Idol'|url = http://ratedrnb.com/2016/01/interview-candice-glover-talks-life-after-american-idol/|website = Rated R&B|access-date = 2016-01-31|language = en-US}}</ref>\n\nShe returned to ''Idol'' for the series finale on April 7, 2016. She performed with all the returning alumni to open the show, singing \"[[One Voice (Barry Manilow album)|One Voice]].\" Later, she performed \"[[Joy to the World]]\" with [[Melinda Doolittle]].\n\n== Broadway ==\nGlover will sing on [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] in the show \u201cHome For the Holidays, Live on Broadway\u201d which is being presented November 17 to December 30, 2017, at the [[August Wilson Theatre]]. Other vocal performers include [[Josh Kaufman]], [[Bianca Ryan]], [[Peter Hollens]] and [[Evynne Hollens]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newyorkcitytheatre.com/theaters/augustwilsontheater/home-for-the-holidays.php|accessdate=14 October 2017|title=Home For The Holidays Live on Broadway|work=New York City Theatre}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nGlover says she wants to be a counselor to help girls through what she went through as a teenager. [[Nicki Minaj]] broke down in tears after Glover's performance of \"[[Next to Me (Emeli Sand\u00e9 song)|Next to Me]]\", saying that Glover has gotten so much more confident during her time on the show. Glover said she would never wear a dress on ''Idol'', but she eventually wore one during her performance of \"[[Somewhere (song)|Somewhere]],\" \"[[You've Changed (song)|You've Changed]]\" by Billie Holiday and the finale. After this, girls began tweeting her saying she was their inspiration and that she made them feel more confident. Her musical influences include [[Christina Aguilera]], [[Jazmine Sullivan]] and [[Brandy Norwood|Brandy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=npKU1GFBUXs |title=Strong voiced @candiceai12 talks to @christrondsen at @americanidol press tent |publisher=YouTube |date= |accessdate=2014-08-10}}</ref> In 2011, Sullivan retweeted Glover's YouTube cover of \"[[Chasing Pavements]]\" by [[Adele]] and called it \"amazing\". Glover once again performed this song on the finale of ''American Idol''.\n\n== Discography ==\n=== Studio albums ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"2\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Sales\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Billboard 200|US]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/1565076/candice-glover/chart?f=305|title=Candice Glover|work=billboard.com|accessdate=5 February 2015}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[R&B Albums|US<br>R&B]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/1565076/candice-glover/chart?f=1235|title=Candice Glover|work=billboard.com|accessdate=5 February 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Music Speaks]]''\n|\n* Released: February 18, 2014\n* Label: [[19 Entertainment|19]], [[Interscope Records|Interscope]]\n* Format: [[Compact disc|CD]], [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| 14 || 3\n|\n* US: 65,000<ref>{{cite news|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/speakeasy/2016/01/06/american-idol-stars-ranked-by-album-sales/|title='American Idol' Stars, Ranked by Album Sales|last=Ayers|first=Mike|work=Wall Street Journal|date=January 6, 2016|accessdate=January 8, 2016}}</ref>\n\n|}\n\n=== Singles ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10em;\" rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! colspan=\"3\" scope=\"col\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|- style=\"font-size:smaller;\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:4.5em;font-size:100%;\"| [[Billboard Hot 100|US]]<br/><ref name=\"Candice Glover Chart History\">{{cite news| url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/1565076/candice-glover/chart|title=Candice Glover Chart History|work=Billboard|accessdate=March 12, 2014}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:4.5em;font-size:100%;\"| [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|US<br>R&B]]<br><ref name=\"Bronson\">{{cite news| url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/idol-worship/american-idol-charts-candice-glover-555317 | work=The Hollywood Reporter | first=Fred | last=Bronson | title='American Idol' on the Charts: Candice Glover, Kree Harrison Make Their Billboard Debuts | date=23 May 2013}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:4.5em;font-size:100%;\"| [[Top Heatseekers|US<br>Heat]]<br><ref name=\"Candice Glover\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/1565076/candice-glover/chart?f=887|title=Candice Glover|work=billboard.com|accessdate=5 February 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2013\n! scope=\"row\" | \"[[I Am Beautiful]]\"\n| 93 || 33 ||6\n|{{Non-album single}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Cried\"\n| \u2014 || 16 || \u2014\n| ''Music Speaks''\n|-\n| 2018\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Break Me\"\n|  \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| ''TBA''\n|}\n\n=== Promotional singles ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10em;\" rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"3\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|- style=\"font-size:smaller;\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:4.5em;font-size:100%;\"| [[Billboard Hot 100|US]]<br/><ref name=\"Candice Glover Chart History\"/>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:4.5em;font-size:100%;\"| [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|US<br>R&B]]<br><ref name=\"Bronson\"/>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:4.5em;font-size:100%;\"| [[Top Heatseekers|US<br>Heat]]<br><ref name=\"Candice Glover\"/>\n|-\n| 2014\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Passenger\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| ''Music Speaks''\n|-\n| 2017\n! scope=\"row\" | \"My Mistake\" <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/My-Mistake-Candice-Glover/dp/B06XNTQBYK|title=Candice Glover 'My Mistake'|work=[[Amazon (company)|Amazon.com]]|accessdate=16 October 2017}}</ref>\n|  \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| ''TBA''\n|}\n\n=== Music videos ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Title\n|-\n|2013\n|\"Cried\"\n|}\n\n== Filmography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Television roles\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n!Notes\n|-\n|2012\u20132014\n|''[[American Idol]]'' \n|Herself / Contestant\n|14 episodes\n|-\n| 2013\n|''[[Disney Parks Christmas Day Parade]]''\n| Herself / Performer\n|TV Special\n|-\n| 2013\n|''[[A Capitol Fourth]]''\n|Television film\n|Herself / Performer\n|-\n| 2013\n|''[[Live with Regis and Kathie Lee]]''\n| Herself / Musical Guest\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2014\n|''[[The View (talk show)|The View]]''\n| Herself / Musical Guest\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2014\n|''[[Northpole (film)|Northpole]]''\n|Josephine\n|Television film\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Underground (TV series)|Underground]]''\n|Gullah Woman #1\n|Episodes: \"Contraband\" and \"Things Unsaid\"\n|-\n|2019\n|''GRITS: Girls Raised in the South''\n|Tiana\n|\n|}\n\n==See also==\n{{Wikipedia books}}\n*[[List of Idols winners|List of ''Idols'' winners]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.candiceglover-official.com}}\n* {{Discogs artist}}\n* [http://www.americanidol.com/contestants/season_12/candice-glover Candice Glover] on ''[[American Idol]]''\n* {{IMDb name|5086206|Candice Glover}}\n\n{{American Idol}}\n{{American Idol 12}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Glover, Candice}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American Idol winners]]\n[[Category:American rhythm and blues singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:American gospel singers]]\n[[Category:American female singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:People from Beaufort, South Carolina]]\n[[Category:Actresses from South Carolina]]\n[[Category:Singers from South Carolina]]\n[[Category:African-American actresses]]\n[[Category:African-American female singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:African-American singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:African-American Christians]]\n[[Category:19 Recordings artists]]\n[[Category:Interscope Records artists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:Songwriters from South Carolina]]\n[[Category:American contemporary R&B singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women singers]]\n[[Category:People from Saint Helena Island, South Carolina]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name = Candice Glover\n| image = Life Ball 2014 red carpet 092 Candice Glover.jpg\n| caption = Candice Glover in 2014\n| background = solo_singer\n| birth_name = Candice Rickelle Glover\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1989|11|22}}\n| birth_place = [[Beaufort, South Carolina]]\n| origin = [[St. Helena Island, South Carolina]], United States\n| years_active = 2010\u2013present\n| label = [[Interscope Records|Interscope]], [[19 Recordings|19]], [[Independent record label|Independent]]\n| genre = [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]], [[Jazz music|jazz]], [[Pop music|pop]], [[Soul music|soul]]\n| occupation = [[Singing|Singer]], [[songwriter]], [[actress]]\n| instrument = [[Vocals]]\n|website      = {{URL|http://www.candiceglover-official.com }}\n}}\n\n'''Candice Rickelle Glover''' (born November 22, 1989) is an American R&B singer and actress who won the [[American Idol (season 12)|twelfth season]] of ''[[American Idol]]''.<ref name=\"top10\">{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/idol-worship/american-idol-top-10-revealed-426777 |title = 'American Idol': Top 10 Revealed Amid Brutal Eliminations |date=7 March 2013 |accessdate=7 March 2013 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |first=Erin |last=Carlson}}</ref> Glover is the first winner to have auditioned three times before being cast for the live shows. Her debut album ''[[Music Speaks]]'' was released on February 18, 2014.<ref name=\"Hollywood Reporter\">{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/idol-worship/american-idol-candice-glovers-album-639324 |title='American Idol': Candice Glover's Album Delayed |publisher=Hollywood Reporter |date=2013-09-30 |accessdate=2014-08-10}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nCandice Rickelle Glover was born on November 22, 1989 in [[Beaufort, South Carolina]], to John and Carole Glover. She is the oldest of seven children.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.islandpacket.com/2013/02/26/2395399/lowcountry-native-aims-for-top.html |title=Lowcountry native Candice Glover in Top 20 on American Idol |date=26 February 2013 |accessdate=15 March 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130302020117/http://www.islandpacket.com/2013/02/26/2395399/lowcountry-native-aims-for-top.html |archive-date=2 March 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.islandpacket.com/2013/03/03/2400313/candice-glover-goes-back-to-american.html |title = Candice Glover goes back to 'American Idol' for third time with win in mind |date=3 March 2013 |accessdate=15 March 2013}}</ref> She graduated from [[Beaufort High School]] in 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.islandpacket.com/2013/03/15/2421553/hundreds-turn-out-to-beaufort.html |title = VIDEO: Hundreds turn out to Beaufort rally for 'American Idol' contestant Candice Glover |date=15 March 2013}}</ref> Before Idol, Candice was insecure and struggled with her weight. In an interview, she said she had to have counseling at school because of her insecurity issues.\n\n== ''American Idol'' ==\n{{Main|American Idol (season 9)|l1=American Idol seasons 9|American Idol (season 11)|l2=11|American Idol (season 12)|l3=12}}\n\n=== Overview ===\nGlover auditioned in [[Charlotte, North Carolina]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hollywoodlife.com/2013/01/24/american-idol-candice-glover-audition-video-best-this-season/  |title='American Idol': Candice Glover Returns \u2014 'Best Audition This Season' |date= January 23, 2013 |accessdate=March 18, 2013}}</ref> She previously auditioned in the [[American Idol (season 9)|ninth]] and [[American Idol (season 11)|eleventh]] seasons. In the ninth season [[Simon Cowell]] said that he could not see Glover being anything more than a lounge singer and she was cut during the final 70 round. She was eliminated by producers during the ninth season when she forgot the lyrics to her song \"[[Chasing Pavements]]\" by [[Adele]].\n\n=== Season 11 ===\nGlover auditioned in [[Savannah, Georgia]]. She sang \"Blame It on Me\" by [[Chrisette Michele]]. She advanced, but her audition was not aired. In round one, she performed Karina's \"Slow Motion\". In round three, she sang \"[[Someone like You (Adele song)|Someone like You]]\" by [[Adele]], where she received a standing ovation from the judges. She performed \"[[It Doesn't Matter Anymore]]\" by [[Buddy Holly]] with eleventh season finalists [[DeAndre Brackensick]] and [[Jessica Sanchez]] in the group round and was eliminated.\n\n=== Season 12 ===\nDuring her audition for the twelfth season, Glover sang \"[[Syrup & Honey]]\" by [[Duffy (singer)|Duffy]], where she received a standing ovation. Judge [[Randy Jackson]] said that she was the best performer by far in the competition. [[Mariah Carey]] called her singing \"The best singing we have heard thus far.\" Glover advanced to Hollywood. In an interview, she said, \"I thought they were going to get sick of seeing my face.\" For the first round in Hollywood, she sang \"Impossible\" by [[Christina Aguilera]]. For the second round, she performed \"[[Hit Em Up Style]]\" with Kamaria Ousley, Denise Jackson, and Melinda Ademi. This was named the best group the judges had seen all day. In round three, she put a jazzy twist on [[Alicia Keys]]'s \"[[Girl on Fire (song)|Girl on Fire]]\". It was later announced that Glover was one of the top 20 girls of the season and she advanced to Las Vegas. In Vegas, she performed \"[[Natural Woman]]\" by [[Aretha Franklin]]. In the semi-finals of the competition, Glover performed \"[[Ordinary People (John Legend song)|Ordinary People]]\" by [[John Legend]]. On March 7, 2013, she was voted into the Top 10.<ref name=\"top10\"/> Her Top 10 performance of \"[[I (Who Have Nothing)]]\" by [[Ben E. King]] earned her enough votes to land among the night\u2019s top three contestants, along with [[Kree Harrison]] and [[Angie Miller (American singer)|Angie Miller]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://popwatch.ew.com/2013/03/14/american-idol-2013-results-top-10/ |title='American Idol' results: First of Top 10 to go is.... |date=March 14, 2013 |accessdate=March 18, 2013}}</ref> After her Top 6 performances, Glover earned enough votes to land in the night's top two contestants, along with Kree Harrison. She covered \"Lovesong\" by The Cure and broke down in tears after receiving a standing ovation. For the first time, after her Top 4 performance, she landed in the bottom two. On May 16, Glover won the contest and her debut single '[[I Am Beautiful]]' was released to music store outlets.\n\n=== Performances and results ===\n\n==== Season 9 ====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!Episode\n!Theme\n!Song choice\n!Original artist\n!Order #\n!Result\n|-\t\n|Audition\n|Auditioner's Choice\n|colspan=2|Not aired\n|N/A\n|Advanced\n|-\n|Hollywood Round, Part 1\n|A capella\n|colspan=2|Not aired\n|N/A\n|Advanced\n|-\n|Hollywood Round, Part 2\n|Group Performance\n|\"[[Superwoman (Alicia Keys song)|Superwoman]]\"<br /> <small>with Shelby Dressel, Kelsey Laverack Rey, and Audri Vargas</small>\n|[[Alicia Keys]]\n|N/A\n|Advanced\n|-\n|Hollywood Round, Part 3\n|Solo\n|colspan=2|Not aired\n|N/A\n|Eliminated\n|}\n\n==== Season 11 ====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!Episode\n!Theme\n!Song choice\n!Original artist\n!Order #\n!Result\n|-\t\n|Audition\n|Auditioner's Choice\n|\"[[Blame It on Me (Chrisette Michele song)|Blame It on Me]]\"\n|[[Chrisette Michele]]\n|N/A\n|Advanced\n|-\n|Hollywood Round, Part 1\n|A Capella\n|\"[[Slow Motion (Lee.M and J. Pearl song)|Slow Motion]]\"\n|[[Lee Mulhern|Lee.M]] & [[J. Pearl]]\n|N/A\n|Advanced\n|-\n|Hollywood Round, Part 2\n|Group Performance\n|colspan=2|Not aired<br /> <small>with [[Lauren Daigle]], Amber Caparas, Brittany Hammond, and Kalyn McNeil</small>\n|N/A\n|Advanced\n|-\n|Hollywood Round, Part 3\n|Solo\n|\"[[Someone like You (Adele song)|Someone like You]]\"\n|[[Adele]]\n|N/A\n|Advanced\n|-\n|Las Vegas Round\n|Group Performance\n|\"[[It Doesn't Matter Anymore]]\"<br/>with [[DeAndre Brackensick]] and [[Jessica Sanchez]]\n|[[Buddy Holly]]\n|N/A\n|Eliminated\n|}\n\n==== Season 12 ====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!Episode\n!Theme\n\n!Song choice\n!Original artist\n!Order #\n!Result\n|-\t\n|Audition\n|Auditioner's Choice\n|\"[[Syrup & Honey]]/[[Call Me Maybe]]\"\n|[[Duffy (singer)|Duffy]]/[[Carly Rae Jepsen]]\n|N/A\n|Advanced\n|-\n|Hollywood Round, Part 1\n|A Capella\n| \"[[Stripped (Christina Aguilera album)|Impossible]]\"\n|[[Christina Aguilera]]\n|N/A\n|Advanced\n|-\n|Holl